{"word":"κάρφος","slug":"κάρφος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>ϰάρφος, ους, τό</el></b> [<el>ϰάρφω</el> ‘dry up, wither’] <b>sliver, splinter,</b> in view of the <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ opp.\">opp.</a> to <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:δοκός\">δοκός</a></el> ‘beam’ a tiny piece of wood is <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ prob.\">prob.</a> meant <b><a href='B:470 7:3-5'>Mt 7:3-5</a>; <a href='B:490 6:41'>Lk 6:41f</a>.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:ἀπὸ\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:κατά\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}